headline.main: Foe at Munda Is Surprised; Destroyers Aid Brilliantly; Enemy at Munda Is Surprised by U.S. Landing; Destroyers Aid Brilliantly in the Audacious Attack

lead_paragraph: ABOARD U.S. FLAGSHIP OF A DESTROYER DIVISION, between Rendova Island and Munda Point, June 30 (delayed) -- An all-out American assault on the Japanese stronghold of New Georgia Island got away to a flying start at dawn this morning. The brilliantly conceived and daringly executed plan caught the Japanese flat-footed; the landing of men and materials had actually begun before the enemy shore batteries opened fire at this destroyer screen.
abstract: Dispatches on: US attack on New Georgia
